name: On Your Marks White Frame
description:
People said I was crazy for daring to dream,
They all laughed at me and said I was over 300 pounds,
They said it was impossible for me to ever become a runner
And you know what? I didn't care.
It wasn't them, the haters, that I was done with.
The haters fueled my fire.
It was my own fears I was done with.
I was DONE with being afraid of failing.
I was DONE with caring about what people think about me.
I spent too much of my life being afraid of what other people think of me.
And while I mourned over all the things I didn't do,
all the things I didn't have,
all the things I didn't become…
And as I sat there, wallowing in my own self pity,
I decided enough was enough and told myself "I'm going to run in that race!"
While people laughed at me,
I used them as fuel for my fire.
And day in and day out was out there busting my ass.
It sure wasn't pretty, but I had to keep moving forward,
It was the only option for me.
Two years later, all I have to say is, who's the one laughing now?

-----


The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. White frames are initially given away for free. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
